  "title": "UPLIFT (School Engagement Programme )|School |Woodlands |Part Time",
  "description": "<p><strong>The Services required are set out as follows:</strong></p><p>• Design and implement activities in the school’s UPLIFT Room so</p><p>as to provide High Needs Students (HNS) with a safe and</p><p>conducive place to be in after school hours</p><p>• During these activities, to also engage and build rapport with</p><p>HNS so as to educate, equip, and empower them with pro-social</p><p>skills and resilience.</p><p>• Provide HNS with a positive adult figure that they can look to for</p><p>support and in times of need (e.g., social-emotional support,</p><p>positive role model).</p><p>• Work closely with school staff to follow up on any concerns</p><p>relating to the student (e.g., safety and well-being)</p>",
